cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.HC, cs.NI, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the performance and resource utilization of distributed computing frameworks (Hadoop, Spark, and DataMPI) for Big Data processing. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper uses a Big Data benchmark suite to evaluate the performance of the frameworks. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the impact of high-performance data analysis requirements on academic and industrial communities. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also possible as the paper proposes a communication library (DataMPI) that extends MPI to support Hadoop/Spark-like Big Data Computing jobs. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also possible as the paper focuses on the performance benefits of DataMPI compared to Hadoop and Spark.
